    "text": "When revenue arrives at an operational project, the contract splits every deposit atomically — the entity never has to be relied on to \"send the investors' share.\" For gross revenue G , a protocol fee rate f , and an investor split s (both in basis points): fee = G × f 10000 , investor = ( G - fee ) × s 10000 , entity = G - fee - investor The fee goes to the protocol treasury, the investor portion enters the yield index, and the remainder returns to the entity — in one transaction.",
